The paper discusses the use of compressive sensing techniques in wireless communications, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of sparse transform-domain representations, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large-scale antenna arrays (cs.MM) and non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) (cs.LG) as potential research areas for compressive sensing in wireless communications.
